\sqrt{8} + \sqrt{32}
\sqrt{8} = \sqrt{4}\sqrt{2}
\sqrt{32} = \sqrt{4}\sqrt{8}
(\sqrt{4}\sqrt{2}) + (\sqrt{2}\sqrt{8})
\sqrt{8}+\sqrt{32}=\sqrt{8}+\sqrt{4\times8}=\sqrt{8}+2\sqrt{8}=2\sqrt{8}+\sqrt{8}=6\sqrt{2}
\sqrt8+\sqrt{32}=\sqrt8(1+\sqrt4)=2\sqrt2(1+2)=6\sqrt2
\sqrt{8}+\sqrt{32}
